 Illinois|McHenry]], [[Naperville, Illinois|Naperville]], [[Saint Charles, Illinois|St. Charles]], [[North Aurora, Illinois|North Aurora]], [[Oswego, Illinois|Oswego]], [[Plainfield, Illinois|Plainfield]], [[Plano, Illinois|Plano]], [[Sycamore, Illinois|Sycamore]], [[Warrenville, Illinois|Warrenville]], [[Wauconda, Illinois|Wauconda]], [[Woodstock, Illinois|Woodstock]], and [[Yorkville, Illinois|Yorkville]]. The incumbent is Democrat [[Lauren Underwood]], who flipped the district and was elected with 52.5% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Lauren Underwood]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pearson|first1=Rick|title=U.S. Rep. Lauren Underwood makes it official: She'll run for a second term|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/politics/ct-lauren-underwood-announces-reelection-bid-20190629-jnp4xr7j3ree5k7hxxl55funay-story.html|newspaper=Chicago Tribune|date=June 29, 2019|accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Endorsements=====\n{{endorsements box\n|title = Lauren Underwood\n| width= 68em\n|list =\n;Individuals\n*[[Alex Hirsch]], writer, artist, and animator<ref>{{cite web | url=https://docquery.fec.gov/cgi-bin/fecimg/?201910159163922373 |title = Page by Page Report Display (Page 850 of 1022)}}</ref>\n;Organizations\n* [[314 Action]]<ref name=\"314Action\" />\n* [[League of Conservation Voters]] Action Fund<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sittenfeld |first1=Tiernan |title=LCV Action Fund Announces Second Round of 2020 Environmental Majority Makers|url=https://www.lcv.org/article/lcv-action-fund-announces-second-round-2020-environmental-majority-makers/ |website=League of Conservation Voters |publisher=LCV Action Fund |language=en |date=August 15, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Sierra Club]]<ref name=\"SierraClub\"/>\n}}\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [