 Hill, Orland, and back.|first=Marie|last=Newman|date=October 31, 2019|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Sunrise Movement]] (National)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/sunrisemvmt/status/1205136536787914752|title=.@Marie4Congress is running to create goods jobs for her district & improve quality of life through a #GreenNewDeal. Her opponent, Dan Lipinski, voted for the Keystone XL pipeline & has taken $37,000 from Big Oil PACs this year alone. |first=Sunrise|last=Movement &nbsp;\ud83c\udf05|date=December 12, 2019|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Sunrise Movement]] Chicago<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Marie4Congress/status/1204432443912212481|title=Thank you for your endorsement, @SunriseMvmtChi! We are in a climate crisis, and we are all first responders. Now is the time to take action to ensure a livable planet for ourselves and generations to come. |first=Marie|last=Newman|date=December 10, 2019|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n* The Executive Board of the Illinois Postal Workers Union<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Marie4Congress/status/1130465743139737601|title=I'm proud to receive the endorsement of the executive board of the Illinois Postal Workers Union. I pledge to fight for fair wages, safe working conditions, and ensuring workers are receiving proper resources. With strong unions, workers and their families thrive! |first=Marie|last=Newman|date=May 20, 2019|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n* The People's Lobby<ref name=\"marienewmanforcongress.com\"/>\n*[[UNITE HERE]] Local 1<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Marie4Congress/status/1237138928416808965|title=So thankful to earn the endorsement of UNITE HERE Local 1! Together we will keep fighting for fair wages, better health care, and strengthening organized labor. #NewDayInIL03 #IL03pic.twitter.com/rNRVYpXUdV|first=Marie|last=Newman|date=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n*Vote ProChoice<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Marie4Congress/status/1212892719716143109|t