dge]], [[Northlake, Illinois|Northlake]], [[River Grove, Illinois|River Grove]], [[Schiller Park, Illinois|Schiller Park]], and [[Oakbrook Terrace, Illinois|Oakbrook Terrace]]. The incumbent is Democrat [[Mike Quigley (politician)|Mike Quigley]], who was re-elected with 76.7% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Mike Quigley (politician)|Mike Quigley]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Brian Burns<ref name=\"ILcand\"/>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results<ref name=PoliticoResults />\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Mike Quigley (politician)|Mike Quigley]] ([[incumbent]])\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 81,720\n| percentage = 75.2\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Brian Burns\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 26,925\n| percentage = 24.8\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 108,645\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*Tom Hanson, nominee for Illinois's 5th congressional district in [[2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Illinois#District 5|2018]]<ref name=\"ILcand\"/>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Kimball Ladien<ref name=\"ILcand\"/>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results<ref name=PoliticoResults />\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Tom Hanson\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 8,640\n| percentage = 83.5\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Kimball Ladien\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 1,711\n| percentage = 16.5\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 10