eneral election===\n====Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Illinois's 10th congressional district, 2020\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Valerie Ramirez Mukherjee\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \t\n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Brad Schneider]] (incumbent)\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==District 11==\n{{see also|Illinois's 11th congressional district}}\nThe 11th district covers the southwestern and western [[Chicago]] suburbs, including all or parts of [[Aurora, Illinois|Aurora]], [[Bolingbrook, Illinois|Bolingbrook]], [[Darien, Illinois|Darien]], [[Joliet, Illinois|Joliet]], [[Montgomery, Illinois|Montgomery]], [[Naperville, Illinois|Naperville]], [[Lisle, Illinois|Lisle]], [[Downers Grove, Illinois|Downers Grove]], [[New Lenox, Illinois|New Lenox]], [[Shorewood, Illinois|Shorewood]] and [[Woodridge, Illinois|Woodridge]]. The incumbent is Democrat [[Bill Foster (politician)|Bill Foster]], who was re-elected with 63.8% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Bill Foster (politician)|Bill Foster]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref name=\"ILcand\"/>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n* Rachel Ventura, [[Will County, Illinois|Will County]] board member<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ortiz|first1=Alex|title=Foster draws 2020 primary challenge from Will County Board member|url=https://www.mysuburbanlife.com/2019/07/18/foster-draws-2020-primary-challenge-from-will-county-board-member/auem5j1/|newspaper=mySuburbanLife|date=July 19, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Endorsements====\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Bill Foster\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;Organizations\n* [[314 Action]]<ref name=\"314Action\" />\n* [[J Street PAC]]<ref name=\"JStreet\" />\n* [[Planned Parenthood Action Fund]]<ref name=\"PP\" />\n* [[Sierra Club]]<ref name=\"SierraClub\"/>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Rachel Ventura\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;Individuals\n* [[Paul Dillon]], actor<ref name=VenturaEndorsements>{{cite web|url=https://www.rachelfventura.com/endorsements/|title=Endorsements|work=Rachel Ventura For US Congress, District 11|accessdate=February 3, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Shannon]], actor, director, and musician<ref name=VenturaEndorsements/>\n;Unions\n* Illinois Nurses Association<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ElectVentura/status/1236992676983189505|title=I am proud to be endorsed by the Illinois Nurses Association. INA has been the voice of Registered Nurses for over 100 years and currently represents more than 3,600 professional nurses across the state of Illinois. I am honored to have their support.|author=Rachel Ventura|via=Twitter|date=|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n;Organizations\n* Blue America<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blueamerica.crooksandliars.com/2020/03/08/rachel-ventura-working-to-unite-bernie-and-elizabeth-supporters/|title=Rachel Ventura Working To Unite Bernie And Elizabeth Supporters|website=Blue America|first=Howie|last=Klein|date=March 8, 2020|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Brand New Congress]]<ref name=VenturaEndorsements/>\n* [[Democratic Socialists of America]] - West Suburban [[Illinois]] chapter<ref name=VenturaEndorsements/>\n* Matriarch<ref name=VenturaEndorsements/>\n* [[Our Revolution]]<ref name=VenturaEndorsements/>\n* [[Sunrise Movement]] - [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]] chapter<ref name=VenturaEndorsements/>\n}}\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results<ref name=PoliticoResults />\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Bill Foster (politician)|Bill Foster]] ([[incumbent]])\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 44,422\n| pe