 [[Rodney Davis (politician)|Rodney Davis]], who was re-elected with 50.4% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Rodney Davis (politician)|Rodney Davis]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref name=ILincumbents />\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results\n}}\n\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Rodney Davis (politician)|Rodney Davis]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\t\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*Betsy Dirksen Londrigan, former nonprofit leader, entrepreneur, and nominee for Illinois's 13th congressional district in [[2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Illinois#District 13|2018]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Schoenburg|first1=Bernard|title=Londrigan to take on Davis again in 13th|url=https://www.sj-r.com/news/20190411/londrigan-to-take-on-davis-again-in-13th|newspaper=The State Journal-Register|date=April 11, 2019|accessdate=April 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Stefanie Smith, former sex worker and activist<ref>{{cite web |last1=Denham |first1=Ryan |last2=Newgent |first2=Sean |title=Second Democrat In 13th District Race Backs Single-Payer Health Care, Green New Deal |url=https://will.illinois.edu/news/story/second-democrat-in-13th-district-race-backs-single-payer-health-care-green-new-deal |website=Illinois Public Media |accessdate=November 24, 2019 |date=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Endorsements====\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Betsy Dirksen Londrigan\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;US Senators\n*[[Dick Durbin]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailykos.com/story/2019/4/25/1853255/-IL-13-Sen-Dick-Durbin-D-Helps-Betsy-Dirksen-Londrigan-D-Get-Ready-To-Unseat-Rodney-Davis-R|ti