2019.<ref name=\"shimkus\">{{cite web |last1=Lally |first1=Caitlin |title=KMOX EXCLUSIVE: Illinois GOP congressman John Shimkus will not run in 2020 |url=https://kmox.radio.com/articles/news/illinois-gop-congressman-john-shimkus-will-not-run-2020 |website=KMOX News Radio |accessdate=August 30, 2019 |date=August 30, 2019}}</ref> After briefly considering reversing his retirement plans, Shimkus reaffirmed his decision to not run on November 4, 2019.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/11/04/john-shimkus-retires-congress-065602|title=Rep. John Shimkus sticks to decision to retire from Congress|first=Anthony|last=Adragna|website=POLITICO|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*Mary Miller, [[Oakland, Illinois|Oakland]] farm owner<ref name=\"Ellington\" />\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Darren Duncan, [[Vermilion County, Illinois|Vermilion County]] treasurer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vermilioncountyfirst.com/2019/11/10/duncan-announces-hes-running-for-congress/|title=Duncan Announces He's Running for Congress|accessdate=November 23, 2019|publisher=Vermilion County First}}</ref>\n*Charles Ellington, family physician<ref name=\"Ellington\">{{cite web |last1=Sapp |first1=Greg |title=Ellington, Miller Announce Runs for Republican Congressional Nomination |url=http://www.thexradio.com/news/78-local-news/41605-ellington-miller-announce-runs-for-republican-congressional-nomination |website=97.9 XFM |accessdate=October 23, 2019 |date=October 23, 2019}}</ref>\n*Kerry Wolff, vice president of the [[Altamont, Illinois|Altamont]] school board<ref>{{cite web |last1=Perry |first1=Scott |title=Altamont man joins race to replace John Shimkus in Congress |url=https://jg-tc.com/news/state-and-regional/govt-and-politics/altamont-man-joins-race-to-replace-shimkus-in-congress/article_32fedd67-c4a1-527f-8d9d-9a558c793795.html |website=Journal Gazette & Times-Courier |accessdate=October 