ublican [[Adam Kinzinger]], who was re-elected with 59.1% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Adam Kinzinger]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Hinz|first1=Greg|title=Kinzinger set to run for the U.S. House again|url=https://www.chicagobusiness.com/greg-hinz-politics/kinzinger-set-run-us-house-again|website=Crain's Chicago Business|date=August 5, 2019|accessdate=August 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Adam Kinzinger]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \t\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*Dani Brzozowski, activist and chairwoman of [[LaSalle County, Illinois|LaSalle County]] Democrats<ref>{{cite news|last1=Barichello|first1=David|title=La Salle Democrat to challenge U.S. Rep. Kinzinger in 2020|url=https://www.daily-chronicle.com/2019/09/11/la-salle-democrat-to-challenge-u-s-rep-kinzinger-in-2020/amuyrpx/|date=September 13, 2019|accessdate=September 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Dani Brzozowski\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes =\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Endorsements===\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Dani Brzozowski (D)\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;US Senators\n* [[Dick Durbin]]<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1226968007966121986</ref>\n;Unions\n* [[AFL-CIO]] of Illinois<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1220055729647902720</ref>\